Key Match Events: Netherlands defeated Namibia by five wickets to move to the top of Group A standings.
Bas de Leede remained unbeaten on 30 to guide the Netherlands to victory.
Jan Frylink bowled a wicket-maiden in the 17th over, dismissing Netherlands skipper Scott Edwards.
Namibia grabbed two wickets in the 16th over, dismissing Tom Cooper and Colin Ackerman.
Netherlands opener Max O'Dowd was dismissed for 35.
Vikramjit Singh scored 39 off 31 balls before being dismissed.
Namibia were restricted to 121/6 in 20 overs.
Pre-Game Insights: Namibia captain Gerhard Erasmus credited the win against Sri Lanka to coach De Bruyn’s efforts over four years.
De Bruyn highlighted the contributions of Albie Morkel and Morne Morkel to the team's coaching staff.
Post-Match Reflections: Netherlands batter Bas de Leede expressed confidence and looked forward to facing Sri Lanka next.
Netherlands captain Scott Edwards emphasized the importance of winning the third game against Sri Lanka to secure a berth in the Super 12 stage.
